dataIdInfo.envirDesc: Microsoft Windows Server 2008 R2 Version 6.1 (Build 7601) Service Pack 1; Esri ArcGIS 10.2.2.3552
dataIdInfo.idPurp: Polygons representing locations of public schools within Bernalillo County.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: Polygons representing locations of public schools within Bernalillo County. These include traditional, charter, and schools of choice. The traditional schools are in the Albuquerque Public School district. Charter schools can be authorized by either the Albuquerque Public School district or the New Mexico Public Education Commission (state).
dataIdInfo.idCredit: AGIS Division, Planning Department staff compiled this dataset based on datasets provided by Albuquerque Public School GIS Planning staff.

Consts.useLimit: School location data should be independently verified. Schools of Choice and/or Charter schools are often in flux and can be added or removed from the public school system throughout the year.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.
Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: Lists if the school is a traditional, charter, or school of choice (alternative school).

Lists whether a charter school is authorized and monitored by the New Mexico Public Education Commisssion NMPEC (state) or the Albuquerque Public School district (APS). Traditional and Schools of Choice are all part of APS.
